bilingual.source: The truck's load exceeded the legal limit.
bilingual.target: 这辆卡车的负载超出了规定的限额。

bilingual.source: Use weights to counterbalance the load on the other side.
bilingual.target: 使用重物来抵消另一侧的负载。

bilingual.source: They are measuring the bridge's maximum load capacity.
bilingual.target: 他们正在测量桥梁的最大负载能力。

bilingual.source: The circuit's load was too high, causing a power outage.
bilingual.target: 这个电路的负载太大，导致了断电。

bilingual.source: The crane operator carefully maneuvered the load into place.
bilingual.target: 起重机操作员小心地将负载移动到位。

bilingual.source: The server's load increased, causing the website to slow down.
bilingual.target: 服务器的负载增加了，导致网站变慢。

bilingual.source: The fanout mechanism helps in load balancing across servers.
bilingual.target: 扩展机制有助于在服务器之间进行负载均衡。

bilingual.source: The poc showed that the system could handle the expected load.
bilingual.target: 概念验证显示系统可以处理预期的负载。

bilingual.source: Make sure to use proper posture when carrying a heavy load.
bilingual.target: 请确保你在搬运重负载时使用正确的姿势。

bilingual.source: Open-circuit voltage is the voltage of a battery when there is no load.
bilingual.target: 开路电压是电池在没有负载时的电压。

list.abstract: Load（英 [ləʊd]，美 [loʊd]），英语单词，作名词为重负；负载；负荷。作动词为向（汽车；船；集装箱）装货；使负载；给…装弹药。短语搭配有loads of（大量；许多）、load up（负荷）。例句为“Arthur has a light teaching load（亚瑟的教学工作量不大）”。 Load相关近义词有charge、working capacity等。

yingyinNormal.en: His job is to make sure that each load of scrap is heated to a precise set of specifications, which means he's constantly on the move between a tiny air-conditioned control room and the 3,000-degree furnace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他的工作就是确保每个负载的废金属加热，到设定一套明确的规范，这意味着他要一直运动在一间小空调掌控室里三千度的熔炉。

yingyinNormal.en: That's a big load on those little shoulders.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对她来说可是一大负担。

yingyinNormal.en: Granny Pig! Load the lunch into the wheelbarrow. Aye, aye, Grandpa Pig.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪奶奶！把午饭放到手推车里。好，好，猪爷爷。

yingyinNormal.en: Granny Pig. Load the lunch into the wheelbarrow. Aye, aye, Grandpa Pig.
yingyinNormal.zh: 猪奶奶，帮我把食物放到小推车里。好主意啊，猪爷爷！

yingyinNormal.en: I know. I guess I am. Oh, my God, load up the Volvo, I want to be a soccer mom.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想我是的。我的天，开着沃尔沃汽车，成为孩奴。

yingyinNormal.en: What a load of bunk. They're trying to extort this lovely young mother-to-be into an abortion.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真是一派胡言，他们是想把这位年轻可爱的准妈妈歪曲成一个堕胎女孩。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, Walker was looking for this big bus load of kids? All right, I get your point. All right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 沃克在找一车子的小孩。我懂你的意思了 （整个周六晚上都在看无聊的电视剧，还不如出去约会）。

yingyinNormal.en: It takes a week to load up the barges with 4.5 thousand kilograms of highly explosive pyrotechnics.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在船上装烟花用了一周共有四千五百公斤威力巨大的烟花。

yingyinNormal.en: At 2:00 p.m., we load the van. J.P. drives. We drop Jean-Louis, Annie and Albert at the North Tower.
yingyinNormal.zh: 下午2点上车，杰P开车，尚路易、安妮和亚博在北塔下车。

yingyinNormal.en: My job is quite complicated. I take big numbers, transmit them and calculate their load bearing tangents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的工作有点复杂，我就是对很大的数字做数字变换计算他们的切线存在。

yingyinNormal.en: My job is quite complicated. I take big numbers, transmit them and calculate their load bearing tangents.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的工作有点复杂，我就是对很大的数字做数字变换计算他们的切线存在。

yingyinNormal.en: I've been working late every night. All I asked was that he clean the apartment and do one load of laundry.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我每天都工作到很晚，我只不过是要求他把家里收拾干净，洗一次衣服。

yingyinNormal.en: Mr. Bull is bringing Mr. Gnome a truck load of new friends. Yippee. But gardens are for plants, not plastic.
yingyinNormal.zh: 公牛先生给玩偶先生带来了整整一车的新朋友。太棒了。但是花园是用来种植物的，不是用来放塑料的。

yingyinNormal.en: All righty. Some non-affect hesitation. Little cognitive D. And a fuck load of aggression, courtesy of those morons in narrative.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我来看看，有一些不影响运行的口吃，有点认知失调，存在大量的攻击性，用来应对故事线里那些白痴。

yingyinNormal.en: But I need to know how to tie the correct knots. I need to know what kind of cable to use the weight, the thickness, the load strength.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要知道如何绑正确的结，要用哪种钢索，它的重量、粗细和强度。

examination_example.sentence: The 240 giant autonomous trucks in use can weigh 400 tones fully <highlight>loaded</highlight>, and travel at speeds of up to 60 kilometers per hour.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 使用中的240辆巨型自主卡车满载重量可达400吨，行驶速度可达每小时60公里。

examination_example.sentence: He <highlight>loads</highlight> up his vehicle with goods that the tribesmen can't easily get and gives the goods to them as a gesture of friendship.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他把自己的车装满了部落成员难以获得的物品，并把这些物品交给他们，以示友谊。

examination_example.sentence: Harrell and Bown believe that blocks were <highlight>loaded</highlight> onto barges during the dry season.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 哈雷尔（Harrell）和鲍恩（Bown）认为，在旱季，砖块会被装上驳船。

sense_info_list.en: a burden of responsibility, worry, or grief

examination_example.sentence: With my institution and teaching <highlight>load</highlight>, I don't have postdocs and grad students.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 以我的机构和教学负荷，我没有博士后和研究生。

sense_info_list.en: transfer a program or data into memory, or into the central processor from storage

examination_example.sentence: So I quickly designed a skirt on my computer, and I <highlight>loaded</highlight> the file on the printer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所以我很快在电脑上设计了一条裙子，然后把文件传到打印机上。

examination_example.sentence: After it fell asleep, they <highlight>loaded</highlight> the cow into a horse trailer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 牛睡着后，他们把它装进一辆马拉的拖车。

examination_example.sentence: And he can <highlight>load</highlight> them onto the shuttle for you when it arrives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当班车到达时，他可以帮你把它们装到班车上。

examination_example.sentence: As clerical <highlight>loads</highlight> increased, something had to give, and that was always face time with patients.

examination_example.sentence: In other departments, a new student is assigned a faculty adviser based on some system of distribution of the departments' advising <highlight>load</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在其他院系，新生会根据院系指导工作量的分配制度，被指派一名指导老师。

examination_example.sentence: Finally I'll be done with my studies and could go on to earning <highlight>loads</highlight> of money.
